Package: SeMiLLa
Type: Package
Title: SEmantic Measurement of Items via LLM Assistance
Version: 2.4.0
Date: 2026-06-18
Authors@R: c(
    person("Jose", "Ventura-Leon",
           email = "jventuraleon@gmail.com",
           role = c("aut", "cre"),
           comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0003-2996-4244"))
    )
Description: Automatic generation of psychometric scale items from psychological
    constructs using Large Language Models (LLMs). SeMiLLa searches for scientific
    information about a concept, extracts theoretical dimensions and attributes,
    generates high-quality items, calculates semantic embeddings, and performs
    Exploratory Factor Analysis (EFA) to validate the factorial structure.
    The package implements a complete workflow: from planting a concept (sembrar)
    to harvesting a validated scale (cosechar).
